	a dprr:PrimarySourceReference ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Mil. 102" ;
	dprr:forAssertion <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/553> .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/441> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #441" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.52.1; Diod. 13.54.1; Chr. 354 (Vivullano et Filippo); Cassiod.; Degrassi 98, 378f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/440> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #440" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Münzer (RE no. 166) identifies Fabius with the Consul of 423, but Degrassi (see 97, on 416) is unconvinced. See 423, note 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/426> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #426" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.47.8 (who omits Fabius, but lists him as Mil. Tr. iterum at 4.49.7); Diod. 13.9.1; Fast. Cap. (A. Sempronius L. f. A. n. [- -]; Q. Fabius Q. f. M. n. [- -]); Chr. 354 (Arratino III et Mugillano II); Degrassi 26f., 97, 376f. On Papirius, see Lübker no. 15." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/398> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #398" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.37.1, and 40.2; Chr. 354 (Arretino et Vivullano); Fast. Hyd. (Atratino et Vibulano), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; on Sempronius, Val. Max. 3.2.8. See Degrassi 96, 374f. For endangering his army in the war with the Volscians Sempronius was placed on trial in 422 and finally convicted and fined in 420 (Liv. 4.37-44; cf. Dion. Hal. 12.6.5; Val. Max. 3.2.8; 6.5.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/397> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #397" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Münzer (RE no. 166) suggested that Q. Fabius Ambustus Vibulanus, Cos. 412, should be identified with Vibulanus. However there is no mark of iteration in any of our sources for 412. See the arguments of Degrassi (97) against Münzer's view." .
